Within the lighter interval (0-85cm) the top portion of the interval (0-31cm) is darker than the bottom portion (31-85cm) although the scale cannot be distinquished by the Munsell charts.

Color variation in Section 5 is muted and occurs on decimeter scales throughout.  The top portion of the section (0-30 cm) is lighter on average than the section to follow, with a very gradual and indistinct contact between the two intervals.  The lighter interval is at its lightest from 16-23 cm. Notably this broader light interval (0-30 cm) lacks glauconitic horizons.

A broad glauconitic band defines the contact between the lighter and darker interval of Section 5, and spans from 28-43 cm.  Glauconitic horizons occur scattered throughout the interval that follows accompanied by brown Zoophycus sized mottles, a sulfide horizon (71-72 cm) and disseminated sulfides (particularly from 128-150 cm). Decimeter scale color variation occurs from greenish grey (5GY 6/1) to light greenish grey (5GY 7/1).

Disseminated sulfides concentrated from 0-34 cm, with brown mottles of various sizes throughout.  Very faint, indistinct green horizons occur throughout, but are more concentrated from 94-113cm.  The color lightens gradually over the length of the interval.
